I take that back. In one of the initial emails FBI sent over, they included a draft agenda. We have since had discussions 
indicating we don't believe significant aspects of that draft agenda are appropriate, so what they sent over is not current. 
But this is what they sent: 
AGENDA 
Welcome & Introductions by Executive Management 
Investigative team: Explanation of dismissal process after Epstein's suicide; explanation of the judicial process; 
importance of interviewing all pertinent victims; all victims entitled to services but not all may be pertinent to the ongoing 
investigation 
FBI NYO: Safety concerns; media interaction 
VSD: Victim rights and services; State Crime Compensation/EVAF 
Open Q&A and Closing 
From: -USANYS 
Sent: Thursday, October 3, 2019 3:49 PM 
To: (USANYS) 
Cc: USANYS) 
Subject: 
Didn't we get a rough outline from FBI of what they want to do at these two victim sessions? I can't seem to find. If you 
have, can you forward to=? 
EFTA00013174
